ovid19-updates/|title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) Updates|website=American Ballet Theatre|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abt.org/abt-to-cancel-2020-spring-season-at-metropolitan-opera-house/|website=American Ballet Theatre|date=8 April 2020|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[New York City Ballet]]\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Lincoln Center]], [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S. \n|2020 Spring Season cancelled.\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nycballet.com/Season-Tickets/A-Message-from-New-York-City-Ballet.aspx|title=A Message from New York City Ballet|website=New York City Ballet|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[National Ballet of Canada]]\n|{{flagicon|Canada}} [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n|2020/21 season revised; world premiere of [[Karen Kain]]'s ''[[Swan Lake]]'' postponed to June 2021; Karen Kain 50th Anniversary Celebration Gala postponed to 24 November 2020.\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://national.ballet.ca/Customer-Message|title=A Message to Our Community|website=National Ballet of Canada|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[The Washington Ballet]]\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Kennedy Center]], [[Washington D.C.]], U.S. \n|Reopen in 27 April; ''[[Swan Lake]]'' postpone to June 2020.\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonballet.org/covid-19-updates-information/|title=COVID-19 Updates and Information|website=The Washington Ballet|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[San Francisco Ballet]]\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[War Memorial Opera House]], [[San Francisco]], [[California]], U.S.\n|''[[A Midsummer Night's Dream (ballet)|A Midsummer Night's Dream]]'' closed after opening night.\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sfballet.org/a-message-regarding-the-covid-19-virus/|title=A message regarding the COVID-19 virus|website=San Francisco Ballet|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Hong Kong Ballet]]\n|{{flagicon|Hong Kong}} Hong Kong<br/>{{flagicon|United States}} United Sta