estra]]\n|{{flagicon|South Korea}} [[Seoul]], South Korea<br>{{flagicon|Taiwan}} [[Taipei]], Taiwan<br>{{flag|Hong Kong}}<br>{{flagicon|China}} [[Shanghai]], China\n|Asian tour cancelled.\n|<ref name=\"Classic\" />\n|-\n|[[Carnegie Hall]]\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n|All rehearsals and performances cancelled until 31 March.\n|<ref name=\"AP\">{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/39fe5e27a796ea41f64d03e540e55266|title=Met Opera, Carnegie Hall, orchestras cancel performances|work=[[Associated Press]]|date=13 March 2020|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[City of Birmingham Symphony Orchestra]]\n|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} Symphony Hall, Birmingham, England\n|All concerts cancelled until mid-April 2020. \n|<ref name=\"Classic\" />\n|-\n|[[Cleveland Orchestra]]\n|{{flagicon|Austria}} [[Linz]] and [[Vienna]], Austria<br>{{flagicon|France}} [[Paris]], France<br>{{flagicon|United Arab Emirates}} [[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]]\n|Europe and Middle East tour cancelled.\n|<ref name=\"Classic\" />\n|-\n|[[Hong Kong Philharmonic Orchestra]]\n|{{flagicon|Japan}} [[Osaka]] and [[Tokyo]], Japan<br>{{flagicon|South Korea}} [[Daejeon]], Seoul, [[Chuncheon]] and [[Gwangju]], South Korea\n|Japan and South Korea shows cancelled.\n|<ref name=\"Classic\" />\n|-\n|[[Johann Strauss Orchestra]]\n|{{flagicon|United States}} United States\n|Remainder of U.S. tour cancelled.\n|<ref name=\"Classic\" />\n|-\n|[[Los Angeles Philharmonic]]\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Walt Disney Concert Hall]], [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n|All performances until 31 March cancelled.\n|<ref name=\"Classic\" />\n|-\n|[[National Children's Orchestra of Great Britain]]\n|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} Lighthouse, Poole, Dorset, England and [[The Anvil, Basingstoke|The Anvil]], [[Basingstoke]], [[Hampshire]], England\n|Spring residency concerts cancelled\n|<ref name=\"Classic\" />\n|-\n|[[New York Philharmonic]]\n|{{flagicon|United States}} 