{"title_page": "12th Golden Laurel Awards", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name          = 12th Annual Golden Laurel Awards\n| date          = {{start date|2001|03|03}}\n| location      = [[The Century Plaza Hotel]], [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| country       = [[United States]]\n| presenter     = [[Producers Guild of America]]\n| award1_type   = Best&nbsp;Producer(s) Motion Picture:\n| award1_winner = ''[[Gladiator (2000 film)|Gladiator]]'' \u2013 [[Branko Lustig]] and [[Douglas Wick]]\n| previous      = [[11th Golden Laurel Awards|11th]]\n| main          = [[Producers Guild of America Award|PGA Award]]\n| next          = [[13th Producers Guild of America Awards|13th]]\n}}\nThe '''12th Golden Laurel Awards''' (also known as '''2001 Golden Laurel Awards'''), honoring the best [[Film producer|film]] and [[television producer]]s of 2000, were held at [[The Century Plaza Hotel]] in [[Los Angeles, California]] on March 3, 2001. The nominees were announced on January 10, 2001.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=PGA Golden Laurel noms come of age|url=https://variety.com/2001/film/awards/pga-golden-laurel-noms-come-of-age-1117791612/|accessdate=September 22, 2017|work=Variety|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170922195007/http://variety.com/2001/film/awards/pga-golden-laurel-noms-come-of-age-1117791612/|archivedate=September 22, 2017|date=January 10, 2001|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=12th Annual Golden Laurel Awards are announced |url=http://www.producersguild.com/special_bulletin/goldenlaurel.html |publisher=Producers Guild of America |accessdate=April 16, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010211184946/http://www.producersguild.com:80/special_bulletin/goldenlaurel.html |archivedate=February 11, 2001 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Producers Guild of America Announces Winners of the 2001 Golden Laurel Awards |url=http://www.producersguild.org/pg/awards_a/awards2001win.asp 